The logo is a guy hanging on a ledge. Well, there's none of that here, no climbing, no jumping sideways or upwards or dealing with difficult passages. This is a forward walking and jumping to lower platforms endless runner. Parkour is more than jumping from high ground to low ground. This game gets very repetitive very quickly, IAPs are fairly forced upon you, the missons are buggy to tick off, and often the very high drops end up in crashes that are impossible to prepare for or avoid. Especially noticeable and frustrating in the weekly challenges. How can anyone get to the finish line? This game is rigged and it's not a pleasant experience, even if you think you are getting better there's no way to improve on guessing how long the next jump should be to avoid a rock you can't yet see. Save your time and especially your money. Just another money-grabber, this time with Enigma-inspired music. Edit: Why do you need "View network connections" permission? Absolutely abhorrent requirement.

content: I want to give this app a good review, but can't with how obvious it is that this is nothing more than an elaborate cash grab. Earning anything takes way longer than it should and the rewards are mediocre, at best. I would say the powerups are, at least, worth unlocking, but they're only worthwhile if you enjoy glitches that make you lose. We all understand the need for money. However, there's a difference between being greedy and earning a living. Fix this game and quit being so selfish.
